Happy_Dragon !!DyDeQuHLG7e Tue 04 Jan 2022 01:14:23 No.44466324 Report
Quoted By: >>44466434 >>44466907 >>44468117 >>44468910
Happy_Dragon here

It's been a while, but I have something new - Sweetheart Deal.
Much thanks to Changed_Daily and the others that looked at pieces of this over the past year.

Sweetheart Deal is set in Nuevo Carcangel circa 2174, about a hundred years after a plague devastated mankind. Billions died and technology regressed, and has bounced back to a pre-atomic level. Some of the anthropomorphic chimeras the plague created live now among the humans.
One of them is Christina Marlowe, a private detective. She's hardly the picture of ladylike, but that doesn't matter to this vixie. What does is her quick mind, her faster muzzle, and enough trickery to make humans and chimeras wary.
In this chapter, Marlowe picks up a new client that appears to be caught up in the fringes of a sweetheart deal. Check a few facts, pester a few people, and call it closed. She knows that cases are never as simple as they seem, but how wild can this one be?
https://www.sofurry.com/view/1804173
https://archiveofourown.org/works/36163999/

Feel free to ask questions. This is a rather complex setting with lots of detail under the hood.
Thanks for your time and for reading.

I had a weird dream last night that I have the urge to share with someone, and I figure this place is autistic enough for it be appropriate.

So in it the dream I traveled by car to a city to visit some family members for Christmas. The city itself was I think supposed to be somewhere in New England, though there was Japanese writing all over the place because I'm a weeb so it could have been Japan, but that's wouldn't make any sense with the rest of the context so forget that.

Anyway, after some mishaps in which I lost most of my money and somehow ended in jail for a crime I didn't commit, I got visited by an anthro dog woman wearing a Santa outfit. I can't give a name for her, but that's to be expected since characters in my dreams rarely have names. She was apparently the Santa-stand-in that delivers presents in this particular region, as exist in all over the world because Santa can't actually be everywhere at once. An anthro reindeer seems like it would have been more appropriate, but apparently she was an anthro Cu-Sith. How a Scottish dog fairy became the Santa-stand-in for a region of New Hampshire, Japan I'm not sure, but I was dreaming so not in position to question things too deeply.

All I know is that it became clear that how she because a one in general. You know how when a guy reaches 30 years old while still a virgin he becomes a wizard? Well in women reach 30 while still a virgin they can be chosen to help magically deliver Christmas gifts to kids, which also applies to female anthro dog fairies I guess.

I don't remember why exactly she visited me. Maybe it had something to do with the subplot in which I was fighting a team of JRPG villains who operated how of an obviously evil lair on a hill just outside town. That may of also had something to do how I got arrested, my memories of the details are hazy.

In any case, she got me out of prison and used her power to appear as a human to help me on my quest to visit my family, evade police, fight supervillains, and gather up money to make my way back home. I had to do a lot of things to accomplish this I don't all remember, though I remember it involved putting on disguises, entering buildings to fight through random enouncter-filled dungeons, and making use of the hot springs inn and loan company that dog santa ran in human form in her off-time. I had to pay her back for all the loans.

I should also mention that in addition to everything else, the dream was also a life sim-type video game like Harvest Moon that had multiple waifus you could potentially romance, and I was aware that dog santa was the secret unlockable waifu similar to how some Harvest Moon games have. At the end I completed all the requirements, saved the day, visited my family and explained what happened, and hopped in the dog girl's flying sleigh to escape the police, at which point I proposed to her and kissed her while flying away while the the rest of the characters waved goodbye. I woke up after that.

tldr. I had a dream were I went on a wacky video game adventure with a magic anthro dog christmas cake and married her at the end.

pics unrelated but vaguely appropriate.

Anon is Isekai into world where anthros exist. I prefer an ALT-universe where sapient anthro evolution co-mingles with human, can be Earth but could also be on a galaxy-wide scale. Anon is not the only human on-world, but humans are pretty rare and exotic for several reasons. Anon has no reason to even try to go back to his original Earth, so his focus is adapting to his new world.

Gate: Jieitai Kano Chi nite, Kaku Tatakaeri would cover a solid conceptual version in many ways, but I'm not really invested in the GATE world dynamics. For instance, magic would be rare to non-existent, but maybe some sort of primitive pagan supernatural. Falling into the new world would be a one-way accident through some sort of portal; no communication or back-and-forth travel. What anon knows is what anon has to work with, and some of it is quite valuable knowledge.

Anthros are not humans with weird ears; anthros are the result of the last 5 to 10 million years of co-evolution with hominids, so their physical, cultural, social forms are highly sculpted by their species origin. Not all of them Earth species. Tech development is more steampunk-tier, formed by cooperative and somewhat paganistic respect for not destroying the world everyone has to survive in. There be Druid-like culture in these parts, also.

The world is less warlike than our Earth. All the different species have been more or less forced to accommodate their vast differences. Not conflict-free, but greater respect for the advantages of cooperation, and much saner religions (mostly).

Anon meets a girl, who is fascinated & excited by proof that alternate worlds exist. She wants to visit anon's world, not knowing the dangers. She & anon have much to work out. Society is a grayscale on accepting mixed relationships, so that remains an unpredictable, daily dynamic.

This >>44486791
A number of species take dust baths, even creatures like water buffalo and many of the cats. Dust gets in between all the fur down to the skin and picks up debris, blood, body oils, etc. Regular dust baths reduce parasites and scent. I have several patches of ground around my house that are little wallows of sand & dust when it hasn't rained for several days. My cats love to roll in it in the hot summer sun. I assume the heat & sunshine help with things like fleas and ticks by making them active, then drys them out and makes them jump off seeking better accommodations. I've also seen foxes roll around in dust patches and, like my cats, they'll go roll around in grass afterward.

So, it's not a stretch that buns probably do the same, given the opportunity. Now that I think about it, squirrels and chipmunks probably do it, too. Probably humans, I'd think, depending on where they live & what conditions. Sounds kind of comfy if I lived in a desert and couldn't take a bath for three or six weeks at a time.
